1.00	Tillab%C3%A9ri_Department	Tillabéri Department	Tillabéri is a department of the Tillabéri Region in Niger. Its capital lies at the city of Tillabéri, and contains the Communes of Ayorou (as of 2001 the largest town in Department), Anzourou, Dessa, Kourteye, and Sinder. Tillabéri is also the capitol of Tillabéri Region. The western border of the Department is formed by the Niger River.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/08/Tillaberi_Arrondissements.png/300px-Tillaberi_Arrondissements.png
